{
  "message": "test(frankenterm-gui): add 7 golden.png pixel-buffer baselines for the GPU stress fixtures\n\nPairs with 311e848a5 (stress fixture JSONs) by adding the binary\ngolden.png pixel-buffer baselines the gpu_regression harness diffs\nagainst. Each PNG was produced by running the harness in\nupdate-baseline mode through the existing\n`tests/fixtures/gpu_regression/` workflow against the Rgba8UnormSrgb\ntexture format declared in each fixture's meta.json.\n\nNew files (7 \u00d7 ~456 KB \u2248 3.2 MB total):\n\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/many-panes-30/golden.png\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/extreme-content-100k/golden.png\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/dpi-1_00/golden.png\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/dpi-1_25/golden.png\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/dpi-1_50/golden.png\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/dpi-2_00/golden.png\n- tests/golden/gpu/stress/rapid-resize-10s/golden.png\n\nEach PNG is the pixel-perfect baseline for the corresponding fixture\ninput.json under the meta.json viewport / DPI / texture format. Diffs\nagainst these baselines are how the harness detects shaper, atlas,\nDPI-snapping, or resize-tearing regressions in the headless render\npath.\n\nSame convention as the existing tracked golden.png files under\ntests/golden/gpu/cursor-*, multipane-*, selection-*, etc. \u2014 the .png\nsits next to expected.json + input.json + meta.json in each fixture\ndirectory. No code changes; this commit only completes the\nfixture triple for the seven stress entries.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
